<script type="text/javascript">
function togPhase(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + n);
	e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';
}
function togAllPhases(display) {
	for (var i = 1; i <= 50; i++) {
		var e = document.getElementById('phasehint' + i);
		if (!e) break;
		e.style.display = display;
	}
}
function addHint(n) {
	var e = document.getElementById('phase');
	for (var i = 0; i < e.childNodes.length; i++) {
		e.childNodes[i].selected = e.childNodes[i].value == n ? 'selected' : '';
	}
	e = document.getElementById('text');
	e.focus();
	e.select();
}
</script>

<div class="mm white">
This quest <span class="blue">[<span class="yellow">2580</span>]</span> is called '<span class="yellow">Spread the Word!</span>',<br/>
for Adventurers levels <span class="yellow">120</span> to <span class="yellow">241</span>.<br />


<span class="hg"><a href="/npc/255">Lord Vendredi</a> [<a href="/area/51">Sigil</a>] is the master in charge of this quest.</span><br />

Make haste!  Make haste!  Haste is what is needed for this quest.  A<br />
great disaster has befallen Sigil.  The beautiful daughter of Lord Vendredi<br />
has disappeared.  She disappeared from her bedroom in this very castle. <br />
Foul play is suspected in her disappearance.  The entire city will be<br />
mobilized to find her.  It is a race versus time to save her from her<br />
kidnappers.  You will visit certain people to relay word of what has<br />
happened.  You are to visit those of importance in Vospire, Sigil, and<br />
Diocletian so they may be on the look out for these criminals.  Also you are<br />
to spread word to the docks in case they try to leave with her aboard a<br />
ship.  Your performance in this quest bestowed upon you will determine<br />
whether she is lost or found.  There are a great many people for you to<br />
inform of these events so be on your way!<br />

<span class="hy">Upon successful completion of this quest you can receive:</span><br />

<span class="hm">*</span>Up to <span class="yellow">150</span> quest points, <span class="yellow">5</span> practice points, <span class="yellow">55,000</span> experience points,<br/>
&nbsp;<span class="yellow">0</span> build points, <span class="yellow">0</span> piety, and <span class="yellow">21,000</span> gold pieces.<br />


You have <span class="yellow">440</span> minutes remaining to complete this quest.<br />

Spread the Word! consists of:<br />


